ShDen Hub servce configuration

1. Installation

Start from hub.servce file in this directory. Check directories layout for everything (node, working directory). 
Make sure hubuser exists in DB, have access etc. Then copy hub.servce to /lib/systemd/system/:

$ sudo cp hub.service /lib/systemd/system/

Run this command:

$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload

Let SystemD know about the hub service and instruct SystemD to load this service on boot:

$ sudo systemctl enable hub

Now run the hub service:

$ sudo systemctl restart hub

2. Operations

To stop the service:

$ sudo systemctl stop hub

To disable the service (prevent it from loading on boot):

$ sudo systemctl disable hub

To see the status of the service:

$ sudo systemctl status hub

To restart:

$ sudo systemctl restart hub